805
01:28:32,995 --> 01:28:37,079
[SPEAKER_14]: It's imperative that cities and towns are careful with their forecasting.

806
01:28:38,100 --> 01:28:47,891
[SPEAKER_14]: We have an obligation to be conservative, and we, on a year-after-year basis, are pushing our own limits in that regard, because if we

807
01:28:48,992 --> 01:28:56,276
[SPEAKER_14]: get too far in our own pushing of our own revenue expectations, then we could find ourselves in a deficit.

808
01:28:56,416 --> 01:28:59,618
[SPEAKER_14]: And we can't really, that's not going to work very well for the city.

809
01:29:01,118 --> 01:29:10,123
[SPEAKER_14]: So when we have a situation where we're not sure when revenues will come in for a specific development, we do our best to forecast for that.

810
01:29:10,283 --> 01:29:13,745
[SPEAKER_14]: But sometimes we have to err on the side of being a little bit

811
01:29:17,556 --> 01:29:17,857
[SPEAKER_14]: Thank you.

812
