02:01:38,482 --> 02:01:43,564
[SPEAKER_06]: So that's why I'm pretty much saying it's pretty conservative because I mean, we're at those numbers.

1182
02:01:44,625 --> 02:01:47,126
[SPEAKER_05]: And this may be for the Chief of Staff, Madam Chief of Staff.

1183
02:01:47,646 --> 02:01:56,510
[SPEAKER_05]: I know in the past that the administration has budgeted kind of a contractual agreements line within the, I think within the executive budget or maybe within the HR budget.

1184
02:01:58,450 --> 02:02:05,413
[SPEAKER_05]: Is that being shifted over in this budget to kind of reflect for some of the agreements that have been settled since the previous fiscal year budget?

1185
02:02:10,517 --> 02:02:10,777
[SPEAKER_14]: Thank you.

1186
02:02:10,797 --> 02:02:15,744
[SPEAKER_14]: Yes, there would be a change, a significant change, because I think historically the number's been over $1 million.

1187
02:02:16,724 --> 02:02:19,625
[SPEAKER_14]: There's going to be a significant change since we've settled contracts.

1188
02:02:19,645 --> 02:02:21,947
[SPEAKER_14]: We don't have any open contracts as of right now.

1189
02:02:22,007 --> 02:02:32,072
[SPEAKER_14]: We are working through negotiations for a contract that will effectively open 7-1, which, you know, another way to say it is that it ends 6-30.

1190
02:02:32,572 --> 02:02:34,773
[SPEAKER_14]: So yes, there's going to be a significant change in those numbers.

1191
02:02:35,313 --> 02:02:37,094
[SPEAKER_14]: That's still being finalized too, but yes.

1192
02:02:37,434 --> 02:02:37,634
[SPEAKER_05]: Sure.

1193
02:02:37,655 --> 02:02:44,358
[SPEAKER_05]: Yeah, I'm just trying to provide some context because obviously if, and you see in a big budget, difficult budget year and then you come to look at this budget and you see,

1194
02:02:45,210 --> 02:02:53,115
[SPEAKER_05]: you know, 17% increase in the salary line, you know, that was actually being budgeted for through this contractual agreement section in the past.

1195
02:02:53,415 --> 02:02:53,615
[SPEAKER_05]: All right.

1196
02:02:53,635 --> 02:02:54,235
[SPEAKER_14]: Yes, absolutely.

1197
02:02:54,375 --> 02:02:54,655
[SPEAKER_14]: Thank you.

1198
02:02:55,216 --> 02:02:55,576
[SPEAKER_05]: Thank you.

1199
02:02:55,696 --> 02:02:55,936
[SPEAKER_05]: All right.

1200
02:02:56,016 --> 02:02:58,798
[SPEAKER_05]: I will go to Councilor Boehling and then Vice President Lazaro.

