1864
02:53:54,761 --> 02:54:08,152
[SPEAKER_00]: Keeping our class sizes that we felt under the CBA requirements, but also keeping things where families felt that their students' needs could be met in a good classroom size.

1865
02:54:10,153 --> 02:54:37,275
[SPEAKER_00]: ensuring working with our COO that he was able to use his strategic skills regarding what capital needs were immediate and some that we felt, as Jerry was saying, we don't want to say the word postponing pretty much the next fiscal year, but understanding what immediate needs we had that we needed to address now, what immediate needs that we're going to talk about later in our free cash request, and also what we can plan for fiscal year 28.

1866
02:54:39,058 --> 02:54:56,386
[SPEAKER_00]: but also wanting to work with our teachers and our paraprofessionals and increasing and improving professional development experiences and providing more professional development to these departments, providing funding for transition, for more rigorous instructional materials.

