[SPEAKER_00]: As we talked about with our enrollment going down a little bit, we did do a net reduction of one classroom.

1920
03:00:57,190 --> 03:01:07,318
[SPEAKER_00]: And as we'll talk about later, we have on our last slide, certain operational costs we'd like to shift over to a free cash request.

1921
03:01:10,200 --> 03:01:19,347
[SPEAKER_00]: Speaking of our enrollment size, so this is what it's going to, this is what the average number is going to look like at the Brooks Elementary, the McGlynn Elementary, the Missituck, and the Roberts.

1922
03:01:20,128 --> 03:01:23,030
[SPEAKER_00]: As you can see here, the numbers are still very healthy.

1923
03:01:23,070 --> 03:01:24,071
[SPEAKER_00]: They still look really good.

1924
03:01:24,934 --> 03:01:28,002
[SPEAKER_00]: And I think these are class sizes that we can be very happy and proud of.

1925
03:01:31,688 --> 03:01:40,737
[SPEAKER_00]: On our next slide, so just to briefly touch on our free cash request, we have here a total request of $530,500.

1926
03:01:41,718 --> 03:01:48,324
[SPEAKER_00]: One of those is for replacing all our defibrillators, AEDs.

1927
03:01:49,345 --> 03:01:55,111
[SPEAKER_00]: They are either, most of the ones that we have currently at the school are outdated and expired.

1928
03:01:56,763 --> 03:01:58,384
[SPEAKER_00]: interactive panels in the classroom.

1929
03:01:59,404 --> 03:02:07,966
[SPEAKER_00]: As we continue to invest in our curriculum, as we continue to invest in our classrooms, we want to have high-quality technology that can meet the needs of our students.

1930
03:02:09,206 --> 03:02:16,307
[SPEAKER_00]: We also have maturity maintenance fundings to address some facilities conditions assessments, estimated approximately at $75,000.

1931
03:02:16,367 --> 03:02:23,109
[SPEAKER_00]: Then last, we have our Roberts water tank heat replacement, but I believe that number, Jerry,

1932
03:02:24,450 --> 03:02:25,951
[SPEAKER_00]: Did we want to talk about that number real quick?

1933
03:02:26,551 --> 03:02:40,921
[SPEAKER_00]: We believe it could change as we're looking to see as technology is getting better, hopefully, we're looking to see what efficiencies we may use that we didn't think about before or as we continue to look forward.

1934
03:02:40,941 --> 03:02:46,445
[SPEAKER_00]: So that number is subject to change, but we're still waiting on all our assessments.

1935
03:02:52,037 --> 03:02:56,845
[SPEAKER_12]: So yeah, this is one of the ways we were able to reduce our budget.

1936
03:02:57,526 --> 03:03:00,291
[SPEAKER_12]: The mayor and the city council have been

1937
03:03:02,643 --> 03:03:10,530
