1981
03:11:25,491 --> 03:11:30,633
[SPEAKER_05]: And if we took that, you know, if we took that and,

1982
03:11:32,365 --> 03:11:42,511
[SPEAKER_05]: did a 3% increase on top of that, then the gap we're talking about is, you know, about $700,000, right?

1983
03:11:43,691 --> 03:11:45,693
[SPEAKER_05]: That includes the 750 this year, right?

1984
03:11:45,713 --> 03:11:46,893
[SPEAKER_05]: So it's still, there's still a gap.

1985
03:11:47,334 --> 03:11:55,938
[SPEAKER_05]: But if we assume that the fiscal 26 base was both the general fund and the stabilization fund funding, because we were talking about that ramp.

1986
03:11:56,999 --> 03:11:58,180
[SPEAKER_05]: But it seems that the mayor's,

1987
03:11:59,382 --> 03:12:03,484
[SPEAKER_05]: kind of budget assumption in that March 1st figure was that the stabilization fund didn't count.

1988
03:12:05,024 --> 03:12:11,467
[SPEAKER_05]: And so that leaves us with more like this two point something million dollar gap.

1989
03:12:11,527 --> 03:12:12,928
[SPEAKER_05]: Is that basically what happened here.

