2002
03:14:06,906 --> 03:14:17,193
[SPEAKER_12]: put that back into the general fund in order for that to be transferred into the stabilization fund and then be spent out over the next three years.

2003
03:14:17,273 --> 03:14:35,146
[SPEAKER_12]: So, that might, that might have caused a little bit of confusion and but, but our position is that however much of a percentage that you wanna increase the school budget by, it should include

2004
03:14:36,106 --> 03:14:41,750
[SPEAKER_12]: that base budget that includes the 1.085 in stabilization funds.

2005
03:14:41,770 --> 03:14:43,111
[SPEAKER_12]: Right.

2006
03:14:43,131 --> 03:14:44,872
[SPEAKER_05]: And so this problem is compounding, right?

2007
03:14:45,013 --> 03:14:47,734
[SPEAKER_05]: Because it'll be like the new base.

2008
03:14:49,095 --> 03:14:49,536
[SPEAKER_12]: Yeah.

2009
03:14:49,716 --> 03:15:03,385
[SPEAKER_12]: So what happens is, you know, in a perfect world we would have been able to spend the whole $4 million and it just would have been, it would have rolled in as part of our base in FY26.

2010
03:15:06,373 --> 03:15:20,142
[SPEAKER_12]: But out of necessity, we had to come up with this plan to keep the promise that the vote is made with us on how to spend that Question 8 money.

2011
03:15:21,803 --> 03:15:22,944
[SPEAKER_12]: But in doing so,

2012
03:15:24,212 --> 03:15:35,821
[SPEAKER_12]: it creates a structural deficit because now you have one-time money funding the budget for a budget that has ongoing expenses.

2013
03:15:35,941 --> 03:15:43,687
[SPEAKER_12]: So it's very important to kind of unwind from that as soon as possible.

2014
03:15:43,787 --> 03:15:50,231
[SPEAKER_12]: And so in effect, there's a difference between, there's a difference of $335,000 between

2015
03:15:54,200 --> 03:16:07,264
[SPEAKER_12]: the stabilization used in 26 versus 27 and that shifts into the general fund in order to maintain the base budget.

2016
03:16:09,205 --> 03:16:23,570
[SPEAKER_12]: And it was designed that way so that that shift would be more manageable than using the whole 2.1 million dollars in 26 and then having to come before the board

2017
03:16:24,137 --> 03:16:33,284
[SPEAKER_12]: kind of replacing that $2 million before we even start talking about collective bargaining and special ed, things like that.

2018
03:16:35,025 --> 03:16:46,493
[SPEAKER_20]: And there were several positions at that time that we had cut previously that were also reinstated as part of the override language.

2019
03:16:47,334 --> 03:16:50,637
[SPEAKER_20]: So those positions were put back into the budget.

2020
03:16:53,779 --> 03:16:53,979
[SPEAKER_03]: All right.

2021
03:16:55,507 --> 03:16:55,928
[SPEAKER_03]: Thank you.

