2051
03:19:02,497 --> 03:19:03,498
[SPEAKER_20]: shifts like that.

2052
03:19:03,518 --> 03:19:08,061
[SPEAKER_20]: A lot of the work, too, that has happened this year is a review.

2053
03:19:08,761 --> 03:19:10,523
[SPEAKER_20]: It's a review of how we've done things.

2054
03:19:10,583 --> 03:19:13,945
[SPEAKER_20]: It's a review of what we want for our students.

2055
03:19:14,666 --> 03:19:24,593
[SPEAKER_20]: And even some of that conversation and that visioning work is also part of the work we're doing that goes into the MSBA for the high school project.

2056
03:19:25,353 --> 03:19:31,598
[SPEAKER_20]: So Jerry and Noel can speak a little bit to some of the things that we've been talking about.

2057
03:19:31,658 --> 03:19:40,365
[SPEAKER_20]: In that first presentation, it, we have always been asked for transparency from school committee.

2058
03:19:40,866 --> 03:19:47,491
[SPEAKER_20]: So a lot of the work that we were doing initially was, how do we want, how do we envision Medford Public Schools to be running?

2059
03:19:48,192 --> 03:19:49,393
[SPEAKER_20]: And a lot of that was

2060
03:19:50,578 --> 03:19:55,201
[SPEAKER_20]: increases in professional development for teachers.

2061
03:19:57,102 --> 03:20:01,124
[SPEAKER_20]: Jerry mentioned at school committee about what the percentage is, it's 1%.

2062
03:20:02,665 --> 03:20:12,010
