2814
04:22:05,536 --> 04:22:05,616
[SPEAKER_02]: Yes.

2815
04:22:08,537 --> 04:22:09,258
[SPEAKER_02]: Councilor Lemming?

2816
04:22:10,978 --> 04:22:12,799
[SPEAKER_02]: Councilor Lemming is absent.

2817
04:22:13,779 --> 04:22:14,299
[SPEAKER_02]: Councilor Mullane?

2818
04:22:14,319 --> 04:22:14,379
[SPEAKER_02]: Yes.

2819
04:22:15,980 --> 04:22:16,900
[SPEAKER_02]: Councilor Scarpelli?

2820
04:22:18,239 --> 04:22:20,221
[SPEAKER_05]: He communicated to me he's having a technical issue.

2821
04:22:20,581 --> 04:22:23,043
[SPEAKER_05]: He is still on, but he can't unmute to vote.

2822
04:22:23,303 --> 04:22:23,583
[SPEAKER_05]: Okay.

2823
04:22:26,306 --> 04:22:27,386
[SPEAKER_05]: So, absent?

2824
04:22:28,547 --> 04:22:30,089
[SPEAKER_05]: You can just mark him as present.

2825
04:22:33,892 --> 04:22:34,152
[SPEAKER_02]: Okay.

2826
04:22:35,053 --> 04:22:39,076
[SPEAKER_05]: I mean, he texted me that he votes to adjourn, but I don't know if that counts.

2827
04:22:39,116 --> 04:22:40,217
[SPEAKER_02]: Technically, I don't think it does.

2828
04:22:42,218 --> 04:22:42,959
[SPEAKER_02]: Counselor Singh.

2829
04:22:44,760 --> 04:22:47,985
[SPEAKER_02]: Vice President Lazaro is absent.

2830
04:22:48,306 --> 04:22:52,432
[SPEAKER_05]: And President Beers?

2831
04:22:52,452 --> 04:22:52,853
[SPEAKER_05]: Yes.

2832
04:22:53,614 --> 04:22:55,758
[SPEAKER_05]: Four in the affirmative, one present, two absent.

2833
04:22:57,040 --> 04:22:58,662
[SPEAKER_05]: The motion passes and the meeting is adjourned.

2834
04:22:58,823 --> 04:22:59,123
[SPEAKER_05]: Thank you.

